message.text:
𝐏𝐫𝐞𝐩𝐚𝐫𝐞 𝐭𝐨 𝐛𝐞 𝐂𝐔𝐋𝐓𝐔𝐑𝐄 𝐒𝐇𝐎𝐂𝐊𝐄𝐃! 🧫

Now that we’re celebrating 𝗠𝗲𝗱𝗶𝗰𝗮𝗹 𝗧𝗲𝗰𝗵𝗻𝗼𝗹𝗼𝗴𝘆 𝗪𝗲𝗲𝗸, let’s also take this opportunity to deepen our knowledge and understand the science behind every result and finding presented to us.

With that, MTSOC now presents “𝑮𝒖𝒆𝒔𝒔 𝒕𝒉𝒆 𝑩𝒂𝒄𝒕𝒆𝒓𝒊𝒂” where we give you a series of questions related to the mind-blowing field of 𝗕𝗮𝗰𝘁𝗲𝗿𝗶𝗼𝗹𝗼𝗴𝘆. Ready to take the dare and put your knowledge to the test?

𝗠𝗘𝗖𝗛𝗔𝗡𝗜𝗖𝗦
1. Check out the photos below— each one shows a bacterial culture on a specific medium.
2. Comment your answer under each photo with the letter of your choice (A, B, C, or D) and the name of the bacteria you think it is!
Example: C. 𝘚𝘦𝘳𝘳𝘢𝘵𝘪𝘢 𝘮𝘢𝘳𝘤𝘦𝘴𝘤𝘦𝘯𝘴
3. Tag 2 MedTech friends who you think would get it right too!

𝗡𝗢𝗧𝗘: Only comments with correct answers and complete format will be counted. Multiple entries allowed, but only your first correct answer per photo will be considered.

MTSOC will be reaching out to the winners for claiming of prizes. 

Knowledge is your best culture—are you ready to grow it?

#PoweredToBeTimeless
#XIIMTSoc
#FEUMTS

Caption by Peachie Corinne Sulit 
Publication Material by Rein Louisse Dela Cruz

message.text:
𝐏𝐫𝐞𝐩𝐚𝐫𝐞 𝐭𝐨 𝐛𝐞 𝐂𝐔𝐋𝐓𝐔𝐑𝐄 𝐒𝐇𝐎𝐂𝐊𝐄𝐃! 🧫

Now that we’re celebrating 𝗠𝗲𝗱𝗶𝗰𝗮𝗹 𝗧𝗲𝗰𝗵𝗻𝗼𝗹𝗼𝗴𝘆 𝗪𝗲𝗲𝗸, let’s also take this opportunity to deepen our knowledge and understand the science behind every result and finding presented to us.

With that, MTSOC now presents “𝑮𝒖𝒆𝒔𝒔 𝒕𝒉𝒆 𝑩𝒂𝒄𝒕𝒆𝒓𝒊𝒂” where we give you a series of questions related to the mind-blowing field of 𝗕𝗮𝗰𝘁𝗲𝗿𝗶𝗼𝗹𝗼𝗴𝘆. Ready to take the dare and put your knowledge to the test?

𝗠𝗘𝗖𝗛𝗔𝗡𝗜𝗖𝗦
1. Check out the photos below— each one shows a bacterial culture on a specific medium.
2. Comment your answer under each photo with the letter of your choice (A, B, C, or D) and the name of the bacteria you think it is!
Example: C. 𝘚𝘦𝘳𝘳𝘢𝘵𝘪𝘢 𝘮𝘢𝘳𝘤𝘦𝘴𝘤𝘦𝘯𝘴
3. Tag 2 MedTech friends who you think would get it right too!

𝗡𝗢𝗧𝗘: Only comments with correct answers and complete format will be counted. Multiple entries allowed, but only your first correct answer per photo will be considered.

MTSOC will be reaching out to the winners for claiming of prizes. 

Knowledge is your best culture—are you ready to grow it?

#PoweredToBeTimeless
#XIIMTSoc
#FEUMTS

Caption by Peachie Corinne Sulit 
Publication Material by Rein Louisse Dela Cruz

𝐏𝐫𝐞𝐩𝐚𝐫𝐞 𝐭𝐨 𝐛𝐞 𝐂𝐔𝐋𝐓𝐔𝐑𝐄 𝐒𝐇𝐎𝐂𝐊𝐄𝐃! 🧫

Now that we’re celebrating 𝗠𝗲𝗱𝗶𝗰𝗮𝗹 𝗧𝗲𝗰𝗵𝗻𝗼𝗹𝗼𝗴𝘆 𝗪𝗲𝗲𝗸, let’s also take this opportunity to deepen our knowledge and understand the science behind every result and finding presented to us.

With that, MTSOC now presents “𝑮𝒖𝒆𝒔𝒔 𝒕𝒉𝒆 𝑩𝒂𝒄𝒕𝒆𝒓𝒊𝒂” where we give you a series of questions related to the mind-blowing field of 𝗕𝗮𝗰𝘁𝗲𝗿𝗶𝗼𝗹𝗼𝗴𝘆. Ready to take the dare and put your knowledge to the test?

𝗠𝗘𝗖𝗛𝗔𝗡𝗜𝗖𝗦
1. Check out the photos below— each one shows a bacterial culture on a specific medium.
2. Comment your answer under each photo with the letter of your choice (A, B, C, or D) and the name of the bacteria you think it is!
Example: C. 𝘚𝘦𝘳𝘳𝘢𝘵𝘪𝘢 𝘮𝘢𝘳𝘤𝘦𝘴𝘤𝘦𝘯𝘴
3. Tag 2 MedTech friends who you think would get it right too!

𝗡𝗢𝗧𝗘: Only comments with correct answers and complete format will be counted. Multiple entries allowed, but only your first correct answer per photo will be considered.

MTSOC will be reaching out to the winners for claiming of prizes. 

Knowledge is your best culture—are you ready to grow it?

#PoweredToBeTimeless
#XIIMTSoc
#FEUMTS

Caption by Peachie Corinne Sulit 
Publication Material by Rein Louisse Dela Cruz

message.text:
𝐏𝐫𝐞𝐩𝐚𝐫𝐞 𝐭𝐨 𝐛𝐞 𝐂𝐔𝐋𝐓𝐔𝐑𝐄 𝐒𝐇𝐎𝐂𝐊𝐄𝐃! 🧫

Now that we’re celebrating 𝗠𝗲𝗱𝗶𝗰𝗮𝗹 𝗧𝗲𝗰𝗵𝗻𝗼𝗹𝗼𝗴𝘆 𝗪𝗲𝗲𝗸, let’s also take this opportunity to deepen our knowledge and understand the science behind every result and finding presented to us.

With that, MTSOC now presents “𝑮𝒖𝒆𝒔𝒔 𝒕𝒉𝒆 𝑩𝒂𝒄𝒕𝒆𝒓𝒊𝒂” where we give you a series of questions related to the mind-blowing field of 𝗕𝗮𝗰𝘁𝗲𝗿𝗶𝗼𝗹𝗼𝗴𝘆. Ready to take the dare and put your knowledge to the test?

𝗠𝗘𝗖𝗛𝗔𝗡𝗜𝗖𝗦
1. Check out the photos below— each one shows a bacterial culture on a specific medium.
2. Comment your answer under each photo with the letter of your choice (A, B, C, or D) and the name of the bacteria you think it is!
Example: C. 𝘚𝘦𝘳𝘳𝘢𝘵𝘪𝘢 𝘮𝘢𝘳𝘤𝘦𝘴𝘤𝘦𝘯𝘴
3. Tag 2 MedTech friends who you think would get it right too!

𝗡𝗢𝗧𝗘: Only comments with correct answers and complete format will be counted. Multiple entries allowed, but only your first correct answer per photo will be considered.

MTSOC will be reaching out to the winners for claiming of prizes. 

Knowledge is your best culture—are you ready to grow it?

#PoweredToBeTimeless
#XIIMTSoc
#FEUMTS

Caption by Peachie Corinne Sulit 
Publication Material by Rein Louisse Dela Cruz
